summary:
The Security Council, 
Recalling all previous resolutions on Lebanon, 
Welcoming progress towards reactivation of Lebanese state institutions, 
Extends the mandate of UNIFIL for one year without amendment, 
Reiterating support for Lebanon's territorial integrity, sovereignty and independence, 
Reaffirms commitment to full implementation of resolution 1701 (2006), 
Expressing concern at limited progress towards a permanent ceasefire, 
Calls for strengthened efforts to implement resolution 1701 (2006), 
Expresses deep concern at violations, 
Urges parties to sustain cessation of hostilities, 
Emphasizes prohibition on sales and supply of arms, 
Recalls importance of respecting the Blue Line, 
Condemns attempts to threaten Lebanon's security and stability, 
Reaffirms determination to ensure UNIFIL's mandate implementation, 
Commends UNIFIL's role and dedication, 
Welcomes Lebanese Armed Forces' efforts, 
Welcomes Secretary-General's efforts to review peacekeeping operations.
Here is a concise summary of the Security Council document:

The Security Council:

Recognizing the need for regular reviews of UNIFIL, 
Bearing in mind strategic priorities and recommendations from the Secretary-General,

1. Extends UNIFIL's mandate until 31 August 2018; 

2. Commends UNIFIL's positive role in southern Lebanon and calls for enhanced cooperation with Lebanese Armed Forces;

3. Affirms commitment to UNIFIL's mandate and calls for full implementation of resolution 1701 (2006);

4. Reiterates call for Israel and Lebanon to support a permanent ceasefire;

5. Reaffirms the necessity of Lebanese Armed Forces deployment in southern Lebanon and requests progress assessments;

6. Welcomes Lebanon's intention to deploy a model regiment and offshore patrol vessel;

7. Urges international support for Lebanese Armed Forces;

8. Calls on parties to respect the cessation of hostilities and Blue Line;

9. Welcomes the Tripartite Mechanism's constructive role;

10. Urges respect for UNIFIL's safety and freedom of movement;

11. Urges cooperation towards a permanent ceasefire and long-term solution;

12. Urges Israel to withdraw from northern Ghajar;

13. Reaffirms call for an area free of armed personnel between the Blue Line and Litani River;

14. Authorizes UNIFIL to take necessary action to ensure its area of operations is not used for hostile activities;

15. Requests the Secretary-General to enhance UNIFIL's efforts;

16. Recalls UNIFIL's role in assisting Lebanon;

17. Welcomes UNIFIL's efforts to implement the Secretary-General's zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation.
requests the Secretary-General to continue taking necessary actions, keep the Security Council informed, and urges troop-contributing countries to investigate and punish personnel for misconduct; 
 Requests the Secretary-General to report to the Council every four months on implementation of resolution 1701 (2006), including detailed breakdowns of violations, restrictions to UNIFIL's freedom of movement, and potential risks to the cessation of hostilities; 
 Stresses the importance of achieving a comprehensive, just, and lasting peace in the Middle East, based on relevant resolutions; 
 Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
